<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xml:id="m2sci_length">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>length (Matlab function)</refname>
        <refpurpose>Length of vector</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Matlab/Scilab equivalent</title>
        <informaltable border="1" width="100%">
            <tr>
                <td align="center">
                    <emphasis role="bold">Matlab</emphasis>
                </td>
                <td align="center">
                    <emphasis role="bold">Scilab</emphasis>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
length(A)
]]></programlisting>
                </td>
                <td>
                    <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
No equivalent
]]></programlisting>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </informaltable>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Particular cases</title>
        <para>
            If <emphasis role="bold">A</emphasis> is a vector, Scilab equivalent for <emphasis role="bold">length(A)</emphasis> is <emphasis role="bold">size(A,"*")</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
            If <emphasis role="bold">A</emphasis> is a matrix, Scilab equivalent for <emphasis role="bold">length(A)</emphasis> is <emphasis role="bold">max(size(A))</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
            If <emphasis role="bold">A</emphasis> contains character strings, String matrix has to be converted to a "character" string matrix using <emphasis role="bold">mstr2sci</emphasis> (Using <emphasis role="bold">asciimat</emphasis> to convert will give the same result).
        </para>
        <para>
            Scilab <emphasis role="bold">length</emphasis> is different from Matlab <emphasis role="bold">length</emphasis>.
        </para>
    </refsection>
</refentry>
